not focusable.

entry.title: [OOPIF PDF] Reorder PostTask() calls in plugin throttle code
entry.content:
When PluginResponseInterceptorURLLoaderThrottle::WillProcessResponse()

is handling a PDF with the OOPIF PDF feature enabled, it must schedule

events such that PdfViewerStreamManager creation and setup completes

before the throttled URL is allowed to resume loading via ResumeLoad().



Currently, the order is backwards, and as such, PdfViewerStreamManager

creation races against network events. Reorder the calls in

WillProcessResponse(), such that PdfViewerStreamManager creation always

happens before ResumeLoad(). With the correct ordering,

https://crrev.com/1229550 can safely reland.

entry.content:
This should have no functional changes.



By using the display::GammaCurve::Sample function we can simplify

the code that sends the LUTs that are sent to DRM (resampling directly

desired).

functions (which are often specified in display color profiles).



This will also allow us to be more intentional about the different

gamma curves that will be specified (those for a color profile

versus those for adjusting brightness as in the chromecast usage).

> This CL makes relevant state changes to the NativeTheme web instance

> when Page colors changes. This is done in the

> ColorSchemeNativeThemeObserver::OnNativeThemeUpdated method.

>

> In the ColorSchemeNativeThemeObserver::OnNativeThemeUpdated method,

> we preserves the current behavior if Page Colors is 'Off' and forced

> colors is false OR forced colors is true and Page Colors is

> 'High Contrast'. However, if that is not the case then:

> 1. Page Colors is 'Off' and forced colors is true, we override the

> state of forced colors for the native theme instance for web since the

> Page colors browser setting takes precedence over OS for web content.

> 2. Page Colors is one of the Contrast themes i.e. 'Dusk', 'Desert',

entry.title: MediaRecorder: Don't provide I420A if CanEncodeAlphaChannel() is false
entry.content:
A video encoder using media::VideoEncoder implementation in

MediaRecorder path checks I420A is provided only if

CanEncodeAlphaChannel() is true.

However, VideoTrackRecoder provides I420A to an encoder even if

CanEncodeAlphaChannel() returns false when ARGB is input to

VideoTrackRecorder. This works with its own h264 software encoder

because it converts ARGB and ABGR to I420A and then drops its alpha

channel. Although media::VideoEncoder for h264 also handles I420A

internally, it doesn't handle ARGB and ABGR. That's said, it depends

on a format whether the encoder can encode alpha channel.

It is more reasonable to convert a format and drop its alpha channel

in VideoTrackRecorder::VideoEncoder common code.



Bug: 1441395

entry.content:

This change only applies to clip path animations, however, this framework can be used for all derivations of PaintWorkletInput.

entry.title: identity.launchWebAuthFlow: center auth window for ODFS over Files app
entry.content:
Get the most recent Files app window and take its bounds, and use

these to launch the auth dialog so that it appears on top of and

centered on Files app (when launchWebAuthFlow() is called from ODFS).



This is to make auth calls from ODFS feel more associated with the

Files app window that triggered them. ODFS does not have its own UI

so we need to make this connection between the extension, Files app,

and launchWebAuthFlow(). We use a delegate for this to avoid overly

coupling the three.



This design leaves space for a lacros delegate later which can get

the necessary window bounds over crosapi. This is why the

GetOptionalWindowBounds() method is async even though it's not

strictly necessary yet.
